Keynote: _Composing programs_ by _Rúnar Bjarnason_
--------------------------------------------------

Coauthor of [The Red Book](http://amzn.to/2nGr89P) of Scala (beware, affiliate link), and an excellent explainer. This was an outstanding close to a very categorical conference. Even though I’m a mathematician, my working knowledge of category theory has improved 100x after learning Scala and seeing how my colleagues here approach problems in a very categorical, functional, typed way of seeing the world. 

{{< figure src="RunarBjarnason.jpg" class="fig-wide" caption="Wat">}}

Unconference
------------

Last year we had a PR hackathon, where together with Carlos we contributed a WIP for regexes to [scala-native](https://github.com/scala-native/scala-native). This year we had more of a workshop/live coding event, where we could choose among subjects. I don’t remember all of them. Raul was there for Freestyle (missed on this one). There was one about writing stuff for Minecraft in Scala... 
Well, I attended what I think were the coolest: how to actually use Akka Typed, with [Heiko](https://twitter.com/hseeberger?lang=en) and a [tour of typelevel libraries](https://github.com/travisbrown/typelevel-tour) and how type classes help in the implementation with [Travis Brown](https://twitter.com/travisbrown). They were oh-so-interesting. 
 
Next year, again and more.
